  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/21225322/Bhai-Hari-Singh-Ji-Amritsar-2.jpg",
  "body": [
    "One of the longest serving Raagis in Sri Harmandir Sahib, Amritsar was Bhai Hari Singh Ji, having served as Hazoori Raagi for 56 years. Bhai Hari Singh Ji was born in 1924 to Mata Gunwant Kaur and Sardar Taara Singh in the village of Kotli in Azad Kashmir now in Pakistan. Bhai Hari Singh Ji started to learn Kirtan at the age of 13 from his father initially, and then he was sent to Bhai Maan Singh Sandhu for further guidance in Gurmat Sangeet. He practiced rigorously for approximately 4 years before forming his own jatha with his brother, Bhai Sharan Singh on tabla and on his side harmonium was Bhai Surinder Singh. Bhai Hari Singh Ji joined in the service of Sri Harmandir Sahib, Amritsar in 1943 and retired in 1999 having served for 56 years. The above information was taken from the book ‘Gurmat Sangeet De Anmol Ratan’ written by late Bhai Nirmal Singh Khalsa. If anyone has more recordings or photographs of Bhai Hari Singh Ji, please contact us."
